title: The new woman and her bicycle
creator: Opper, Fredrick Burr, 1857-1937
description: A man stands straight holding a road bike on his left side with his hands on the handles. The man has a mustache and a wide brim hat, trousers, and a buttoned shirt with a collared jacket.

title: Fashion, world of- Mannequins- with bike
creator: N/A
description: At night a man is riding a bicycle with a long sleeve shirt that says New York with track pants of the same color. his expression is flat as he rides towards the camera. The flash illumated him while the background remains dark.

title: Biking across town
creator: N/A
description: A crowd of riders lined up on the left look intently as if they are ready to start a race. mostly wearing trousers, hats, and white button ups. On the left there are children facing away from the camera riding bikes, while a boy in the right corner looks at the camera. in the background is a field with trees and buildings.
source: Los Angeles Public Library, Photo Collection

title: Betzy Kjelsberg, 1891, in Drammen. Was among the first to start riding on a bike.
creator: N/A
description: Four men sitting in the grass in various different outfits. Two men look to be holding up books. There two bikes standing behind them. The grass looks long and coveres most of the men's legs. in the background is a field of tall grass and in the distance there are pine trees.
